725617f-a.text:
73rd Avenue, north side, at 179th Street, showing the Brinkerhoff House, later the Skidmore House, built about 1700. The house was owned by Hoagland in 1860; by J.Diehl in 1873; and by Schleider from 1891 to 1909. 73rd Avenue
was formely Black Stump Road.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  1922

725618f-d.text:
73rd Avenue, north side, at 179th Street, showing the Brinkerhoff house, the lower half of which is stone and the upper shingled. It was also known as the Skidmore house and the J. Diehl house.
73rd Avenue is the former Black Stump Road.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  Views 1,2,3,4: 1922

725613f-b.text:
73rd Avenue, north side, at 179th Street, showing the old Brinkerhoff Homestead, built about 1700. Later it was known as the Skidmore house and also the J. Diehl house. The latter owned it in 1873. In 1891-1909 it was on the
38-acre farm of Schleider.
P. L. Sperr  Views 1,2: March 31, 1927
